parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause inaccurate readings on the speedometer, fuel gauge, oil pressure gauge, and other essential gauges, leading to potential safety risks, including accidents and speeding tickets.
symptoms: Speedometer stuck or displaying incorrect readings
fuel gauge stuck or displaying incorrect readings
oil pressure gauge stuck or displaying incorrect readings
other gauges malfunctioning or displaying incorrect readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Reduced Engine Power and Stabilitrak Warning
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced engine power and Stabilitrak warning can cause the vehicle to suddenly slow down or lose power, leading to potential accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: "Reduced Engine Power" warning light
Stabilitrak warning light
sudden loss of power
vehicle slowing down or stalling
inability to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause various malfunctions, including faulty gauges, alarm system issues, and loss of power, leading to potential safety risks.
symptoms: Faulty gauges
alarm system malfunctioning
loss of power
electrical issues with headlights
taillights
and interior lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and transmission issues can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to potential accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: Clutch pedal sticking or feeling soft
difficulty shifting gears
vehicle stalling or losing power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause the loss of braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
brake fluid leaks
and the ABS light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Failure and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose control, or become difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering warning light comes on
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the steering feels loose or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column and Intermediate Shaft Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and intermediate shaft can cause the steering to become loose, difficult to control, or even lock up, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
there is a clunking or grinding noise when turning
and the steering becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension and Steering Knuckle Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension and steering knuckle can cause the vehicle to vibrate, pull to one side, or lose control, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or pulls to one side
there is a clunking or grinding noise when turning
and the steering becomes difficult to control.
